     <h3>FAQ</h3>
       <p><strong>How much does the workshop cost?</strong>
      Thanks to our sponsors, the workshop will be free of charge and food/drinks will be provided too. However, please bring your motivation, bags of enthusiasm and your own laptop to learn the basics of programming with us!
      </p>
       <p>
         <strong>Who is this aimed for?</strong>
         Women of any age with basic knowledge of working with a computer. We’ve had people of all ages taking part. Most of the speeches are given in english, but small group work is done in german. Please bring your laptop.
       </p>
       <p>
         <strong>Can men attend?</strong>
         Yes, but you need to be accompanied by an interested lady. Also, girls are given a priority.
       </p>
        <p>
          <strong>What's your code of conduct?</strong>
          Yes! In short, Rails Girls Kumasi is dedicated to a harassment-free workshop experience for everyone. Longer version here: <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=13f0E_5Fl9lpF-FzWeAyCnC4_YR2idpXz">CoC</a>
         </p>
       <p>
          <strong>I know how to program. How can I help?</strong>
         We are looking for enthusiastic coaches to make this day a success! You are very welcome if you know how to program, even if you do not know Ruby on Rails yet or have no teaching experience. The workshop aims to make it easy for coaches too. We will show you! Interested? <a href="mailto:railsgirlskumasi@gmail.com">Email us</a>.
       </p>


